cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes an unsupervised learning approach for multi-modal image registration, which involves image disentangling and factorized latent shape code. This approach is based on deep learning techniques and involves image-to-image translation and adversarial loss. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with multi-modal image analysis (cs.MM) and proposes novel metrics for training the network, which involves neural networks (cs.NE).
